rComments: Bennett is a very good teacher, but her grading is too in-depth critical for a College Nine core course (the other teacher(s) hardly put any effort into grading papers, and people in that course got better grades for less work).  Beware of hints about in-class quizzes about the reading!

Elizabeth is an extremely good teacher for an extremely dull subject. The college 9 core is an absolute joke and has no relation 2 its theme, however she is a great teacher.Essays r straight forward & her feedback on them shows u exactly what u need 2 do 2 improve. I've always been a great writer & my writing only improved under her guidance.

Elizabeth is awesome! She's really lenient and makes sure you don't feel awkward in class during discussion.  She grades pretty easy, as is very helpful in terms of what she wants in your essay and how to achieve. I highly recommend you take any class with her!
This was a great class, one of my favorites, she mixed up lots of stuff-lectures, discussion, movies and it was always really good.

She is enthusiastic about her subject but isn't the most dynamic instructor. She is quite lenient - doesn't give too much work and grades generously. There is a lot of discussion in class which can get frustrating.

VERY cool teacher. Very accessible and helpful, cares about students. Subject can be very interesting, sometimes a little hard, but a pretty easy subject/ class overall, with exception to all the writing. Quite a few papers 2 keep you busy, a lot of reading too. Lectures (when she does them) can be boring, always involves class discussions though.
